article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Braeden Smith's 21 points helped Colgate defeat Binghamton 84-49 on Wednesday night. Smith added nine assists and five steals for the Raiders (4-3). Ryan Moffatt scored 10 points and added nine rebounds. Keegan Records had nine points and shot 3 of 9 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line. Tymu Chenery finished with nine points for the Bearcats (4-4). Nehemiah Benson added eight points for Binghamton. In addition, Gavin Walsh finished with seven points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
